.TH "bpt" "1" "2026-03-12"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
bpt - Bedrock Package Tool
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBbpt\fR [\fIcommon-options\fR] <command> [\fIarguments\fR]
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBbpt\fR is the Bedrock Linux package manager.\&
.PP
It can:
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
install, remove, upgrade, downgrade, and apply package selections
.IP \(bu 4
inspect installed and repository package metadata
.IP \(bu 4
synchronize repository indexes and fetch repository packages
.IP \(bu 4
build binary packages from build definitions
.IP \(bu 4
sign and verify package-related files
.PD
.PP
Most commands operate against a target root selected with \fB-R\fR or \fB--root-dir\fR.\&
If no root is specified, \fB/\fR is used.\&
.PP
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
.RS 4
Display help information.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-v\fR, \fB--version\fR
.RS 4
Display version information.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-y\fR, \fB--yes\fR
.RS 4
Assume yes as the answer to all prompts and run non-interactively.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-D\fR, \fB--dry-run\fR
.RS 4
Show steps that would be taken without taking them.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-N\fR, \fB--netutil-stderr\fR
.RS 4
Print network utility stderr.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-V\fR, \fB--skip-verify\fR
.RS 4
Skip verifying signatures.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-S\fR, \fB--skip-sign\fR
.RS 4
Skip signing results.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-P\fR, \fB--priv-key\fR=\fIPATH\fR
.RS 4
Use the specified minisign private key.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--priv-key-passphrase-file\fR=\fIPATH\fR
.RS 4
Read the minisign private key passphrase from a file.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-O\fR, \fB--out-dir\fR=\fIPATH\fR
.RS 4
Write fetched or built output files to \fIPATH\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-R\fR, \fB--root-dir\fR=\fIPATH\fR
.RS 4
Operate on the filesystem tree rooted at \fIPATH\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH COMMANDS
.PP
.SS install
.PP
\fBbpt\fR install [\fIoptions\fR] <pkg>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Install packages.\&
.PP
Each package argument may be:
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
a repository package identifier
.IP \(bu 4
a path to a \fB.\&bpt\fR binary package
.IP \(bu 4
a path to a \fB.\&bbuild\fR build definition
.IP \(bu 4
an HTTP or HTTPS URL to a \fB.\&bpt\fR binary package
.IP \(bu 4
an HTTP or HTTPS URL to a \fB.\&bbuild\fR build definition
.PD
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-r\fR, \fB--reinstall\fR
.RS 4
Reinstall already installed package(s).\&
.PP
.RE
.SS remove
.PP
\fBbpt\fR remove [\fIoptions\fR] <partid>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Remove packages selected from the world file.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-p\fR, \fB--purge\fR
.RS 4
Also remove modified configuration files.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-f\fR, \fB--forget\fR
.RS 4
Forget package metadata without removing files from disk.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS upgrade
.PP
\fBbpt\fR upgrade [<pkg>.\&.\&.\&]
.PP
Upgrade installed packages.\&
.PP
With no package arguments, upgrade all installed packages that have an explicit installed version.\&
With arguments, each argument may be a repository package identifier, a package path, or a package URL.\&
.PP
.SS downgrade
.PP
\fBbpt\fR downgrade <pkg>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Downgrade installed packages.\&
.PP
Each argument may be a repository package identifier, a package path, or a package URL.\&
Repository downgrades require an explicit target version.\&
.PP
.SS apply
.PP
\fBbpt\fR apply
.PP
Reconcile the current installed package set against the current \fB/etc/bpt/world\fR file for the selected root.\&
This is useful after manual world-file edits or after recovering from partial operations.\&
.PP
.SS check
.PP
\fBbpt\fR check [\fIoptions\fR] [<partid>.\&.\&.\&]
.PP
Check installed package integrity.\&
.PP
With no package arguments, check all installed packages.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-s\fR, \fB--strict\fR
.RS 4
Treat backup file content differences as errors.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-i\fR, \fB--ignore-backup\fR
.RS 4
Ignore backup file content differences.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS info
.PP
\fBbpt\fR info [\fIoptions\fR] <pkg>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Describe packages.\&
.PP
Arguments may be installed package identifiers, repository package identifiers, package paths, or package URLs.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-i\fR, \fB--installed\fR
.RS 4
Search installed packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-r\fR, \fB--repository\fR
.RS 4
Search repository packages.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS files
.PP
\fBbpt\fR files [\fIoptions\fR] <pkg>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
List files provided by packages.\&
.PP
Arguments may be installed package identifiers, repository binary package identifiers, package paths, or package URLs to binary packages.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-i\fR, \fB--installed\fR
.RS 4
Search installed packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-r\fR, \fB--repository\fR
.RS 4
Search repository packages.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS search
.PP
\fBbpt\fR search [\fIoptions\fR] <regex>
.PP
Search package names or descriptions.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-n\fR, \fB--name\fR
.RS 4
Search package names.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-d\fR, \fB--description\fR
.RS 4
Search package descriptions.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-i\fR, \fB--installed\fR
.RS 4
Search installed packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-r\fR, \fB--repository\fR
.RS 4
Search repository packages.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS list
.PP
\fBbpt\fR list [\fIoptions\fR]
.PP
List packages.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-i\fR, \fB--installed\fR
.RS 4
List installed packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-r\fR, \fB--repository\fR
.RS 4
List repository packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-x\fR, \fB--explicit\fR
.RS 4
List explicitly installed packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-d\fR, \fB--dependency\fR
.RS 4
List packages installed as dependencies.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS provides
.PP
\fBbpt\fR provides [\fIoptions\fR] <regex>
.PP
List packages that provide files matching a regular expression.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-i\fR, \fB--installed\fR
.RS 4
Search installed packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-r\fR, \fB--repository\fR
.RS 4
Search repository packages.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS sync
.PP
\fBbpt\fR sync [<index>.\&.\&.\&]
.PP
Synchronize repository package and file indexes.\&
.PP
With no arguments, synchronize all configured indexes.\& Arguments may be local \fB.\&pkgidx\fR and \fB.\&fileidx\fR paths or HTTP/HTTPS URLs.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--force\fR
.RS 4
Refresh indexes even if they were checked recently.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS fetch
.PP
\fBbpt\fR fetch <partid>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Fetch repository packages into the output directory.\&
.PP
.SS clean
.PP
\fBbpt\fR clean [\fIoptions\fR]
.PP
Remove cached package and source files.\&
.PP
With no options, both caches are cleaned.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-p\fR, \fB--packages\fR
.RS 4
Remove cached packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-s\fR, \fB--source\fR
.RS 4
Remove cached source files.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS build
.PP
\fBbpt\fR build [\fIoptions\fR] <bbuild>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Build binary packages from build definitions.\&
.PP
Each argument may be a repository build-definition identifier, a local \fB.\&bbuild\fR path, or an HTTP/HTTPS URL to a \fB.\&bbuild\fR file.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-a\fR, \fB--arch\fR=\fIARCH\fR
.RS 4
Target architecture.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS make-repo
.PP
\fBbpt\fR make-repo
.PP
Generate local repository artifacts, including \fB.\&bpt\fR, \fB.\&pkgidx\fR, and \fB.\&fileidx\fR files.\&
.PP
.SS verify
.PP
\fBbpt\fR verify <path>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Verify signatures on files.\&
.PP
.SS sign
.PP
\fBbpt\fR sign <path>.\&.\&.\&
.PP
Sign files, replacing any existing bpt signature block.\&
.PP
Options:
.PP
\fB-n\fR, \fB--needed\fR
.RS 4
Only sign files which do not currently pass \fBbpt verify\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH FILES
.PP
\fB/etc/bpt/bpt.\&conf\fR
.RS 4
General bpt configuration.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB/etc/bpt/make.\&conf\fR
.RS 4
Build configuration.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB/etc/bpt/make.\&common\fR
.RS 4
Build helper shell functions.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB/etc/bpt/repos/\fR
.RS 4
Repository configuration files.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB/etc/bpt/world\fR
.RS 4
List of explicitly desired packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB/var/lib/bpt/pkgidx/\fR
.RS 4
Cached repository package indexes for the selected root.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB/var/lib/bpt/fileidx/\fR
.RS 4
Cached repository file indexes for the selected root.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB/var/lib/bpt/instpkg/\fR
.RS 4
Installed package metadata for the selected root.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH SHELL INTEGRATION
.PP
The project ships shell completion files for Bash, Zsh, and Fish.\&
.PP
Installed package and world-file aware completions honor \fB-R\fR and \fB--root-dir\fR when those are present on the command line.\&
.PP
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\fBbpt.\&conf\fR(5)
